## The Window Is Narrowing

AI regulation has moved from the periphery of compliance programmes to their centre in a short period of time, and that trajectory is not reversing. The EU AI Act is enforcing. US states are enforcing. The UAE's institutional frameworks are live. The US federal government has signalled where it intends to take national policy.

The organisations best positioned for what comes next share a common characteristic: they have not waited for the deadline to act. They have built AI governance into the way they operate — with a documented system inventory, a coherent risk framework, clear accountability, and contracts that reflect current obligations.

That is the standard regulators, clients, and counterparties are moving toward. The time to meet it is before it becomes a requirement.

